P.Eng. President + CEO For over three decades, Liberty Entertainment Group, led by Nick Di Donato has been redefining Toronto’s restaurant, nightlife and special event experience. As creators of numerous landmark establishments Liberty Entertainment Group has become recognized as one of the most successful and innovative companies in the hospitality and entertainment industry, appreciating a continuous growth and garnering constant media attention. At the heart of this evolving urban development is President and C.E.O., Nick Di Donato. View Full Bio Here Nadia Di Donato Vice President / Creative Director Nadia Di Donato has been part of the Liberty Entertainment Group organization since its inception in 1987. Since then, Ms. Di Donato has worked closely with its developers in creating the individually unique design approaches for each of the Liberty Group venues. Formally trained in visual communications at Ryerson Polytechnic University and as a result of the many years of involvement with the Liberty Group, Ms. Di Donato is able to create synergy between form and function. With particular attention to detail, she has established the Liberty Entertainment Group facilities as the most creatively themed venues in the city. Nadia Di Donato has played an integral role in Liberty Entertainment Group’s portfolio of venues with her unique and innovative approach to design. Nadia’s vision is to create synergy between form and function. She is versatile in her execution combining natural elements with artistry. With particular attention to detail, she has established the Liberty Entertainment Group facilities as the most creatively themed venues in the cities of Toronto and Miami. Recognized as one of the most creative designers in the industry, her impressive roster of properties has garnered her international accolades for her showstopping work. Nadia was nominated as designer of the year 2023 by UK’s design et al, International Hotel & Property Awards and has received numerous awards and accolades from the prestigious award program: Nominated 2025 Best Restaurant Design: Blue Bovine – Global and the Americas Nominated 2024 Best Restaurant Design: DaNico – Global and the Americas Awarded 2023 Best Restaurant Design: Don Alfonso 1890 – the Americas 2021 Hospitality Designer of the Decade (Shortlisted) Awarded 2020 Best Restaurant Design: BlueBlood Steakhouse – Americas and Caribbean BLT Built Design Recognition 2024: Blue Bovine Steak + Sushi House MUSE Design Awards 2022: Don Alfonso 1890 – Dining of the Year LIV Hospitality Design Awards Winner 2021: BlueBlood Steakhouse Interior Design -Historic & Heritage Don Alfonso 1890 Interior Design – Pop up Bar & Restaurant & Historic & Heritage Pat Di Donato Hon H.R.M. Executive Vice President From an early age Pat Di Donato immediately began to set his goals towards the hospitality industry. As an honours graduate in Hotel and Restaurant Management, Mr. Di Donato brings over 30 years of hospitality experience to the Liberty Entertainment Group. As a co-founder of the company, Mr. Di Donato is a dynamic member of the ever-expanding team and continues to successfully develop and manage the food and hospitality aspect of the business. Michael Ewing Executive Corporate Chef Vice President of Operations Michael Ewing, a twenty-five year veteran of the culinary art industry, began a classical apprenticeship at Westin Hotels at the tender age of 15. Working throughout the city in many of Toronto’s top restaurants and catering companies, Mr. Ewing draws upon his many years of culinary expertise and artistry for his role of Executive Corporate Chef for the Liberty Entertainment Group. Mr. Ewing oversees food preparation and presentation for over four hundred events annually and manages a kitchen staff of nearly three hundred. Meet Our Team - Liberty Lane Caterers - Liberty Lane Caterers Style Sampler Layout Style Fullscreen Boxed Mode Patterns for Boxed Mode Backgrounds for Boxed Mode About Our History Meet Our Team Testimonials Events Corporate Events Social Events Weddings Vendors Pick Up Party Menu 2021 Easter Menu Blog FB Contact 8 Merrill Industrial Dr., Hampton, NH 03843 603.926.1545 Book an Event Search About Our History Meet Our Team Testimonials Events Corporate Events Social Events Weddings Vendors Pick Up Party Menu 2021 Easter Menu Blog FB Contact Meet Our Team Kevin Sullivan, Owner A New Hampshire native, and 30 year resident of Hampton, Kevin began his career as the Bar Manager at the Galley Hatch Restaurant in 1985. He became one of the three original founders of the catering company in 1996, and in 2013 bought his partners out to become the sole proprietor of Liberty Lane Catering. Catering is certainly a way of life for Kevin, as he in a hands-on, involved director, and oversees many of our events. He also personally meets with every bridal couple, and has an enormous thank you note collection from past and present clients. Kevin has served on the Governor’s Advisory Council on Unemployment Compensation since 1999, is a board member of the Dover Chamber of Commerce, and is actively involved in the Hampton Youth Association. He is also is a past Chairman of the New Hampshire Lodging & Restaurant Association. He and his wife, Starr have three children, and in his spare time, Kevin officiates local youth soccer and basketball games. Nick Minichello, Executive Chef A talented restaurateur from East Boston, Executive Chef Nick Minichello brings over 30 years of culinary experience to the head of our culinary team.  Before joining Liberty Lane Catering, Nick was the owner/operator of Lena’s restaurant in Hampton for 16 years.  A true Greek, Nick loves all things food and in his free time often donates his catering skills to Saint Nicholas’ Greek church in Portsmouth, NH.  He lives in Hampton with his wife, three children, and adorable dog, Matty.  Fun fact:  Nick once swam across Lake Winnipesaukee! Kristi Datro, Catering Manager The newest member of our management team, Kristi has truly worked her way up in the company. After recognizing her strong skills as an event server, Kristi was quickly promoted to Event Supervisor, and then on to Catering Manager. Her cool demeanor and her ability to manage multiple tasks at once, all while ensuring the client’s expectations are exceeded, makes Kristi a great asset to our team. In addition to a new mid-century inspired aesthetic, we moved the espresso bar to the opposite wall and added a full bar featuring select wines, fresh cocktails and craft beer. SERVING FROM THE HEART We are dedicated to quality food that nourishes the body and the soul We opened Liberty Market over a decade ago to serve our local community, in good times and in hard times. David & Kiersten Traina Joe & Cindy Johnston Owners, Liberty Market HOURS & LOCATION HOURS: Monday - Sunday, 8am - 9pm LOCATION: 230 N Gilbert Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85234 PHONE: 480 - 892 - 1900 EMAIL: info@libertymarket.com LARGE GROUP RESERVATIONS If you would like to make a reservation for 9 or more people, please send an email to reservations@libertymarket.com . Please allow up to 24-48 hours for a response. Due to limited large group seating space, we highly recommend making large group requests well in advance. Please include your full name, contact number, the number of people, date and time of reservation request, and any other details such as high chair or accessibility needs. A member of our management team will reach out to finalize the details with you and then grant you a reservation if possible. Please ensure to provide proper contact information.
